This article is a proclamation by President Donald J. Trump declaring May 13, 2018, as Mother's Day in the United States. The proclamation highlights the importance of mothers in society and acknowledges their contributions to empowering and inspiring others. It also pays tribute to mothers who are no longer with us, particularly mentioning former First Lady Barbara Pierce Bush. The proclamation encourages all Americans to express their love and respect for their mothers and reflects on the significance of motherhood to the prosperity of families, communities, and the nation.